FBIS4-13663 "drnes078_c_94008" FBIS-NES-94-078 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 Egypt Shaykh Denies BBC Report on Antigovernment Acts Shaykh Denies BBC Report on Antigovernment Acts NC2204083394 Cairo ROSE AL-YUSUF in Arabic 18 Apr 94 p 13 NC2204083394 Cairo ROSE AL-YUSUF Arabic BFN [Text] Shaykh Muhammad al-Ghazali has denied a BBC report attributed to him on the morning of 8 April that he is engaged in hostile acts against the Egyptian Government. Shaykh al-Ghazali told ROSE AL-YUSUF that the BBC cited an interview with him conducted by a British journalist from THE GUARDIAN. There was a mistake in the translation, he said. AL-GHAZALI stressed that the report is unfounded. He said he is serving the heritage and message of Islam within the limits of public order. He said he never thought of violating the state's general law.
